org.rdkit.knime.types

Class RDKitMolCellFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rdkit.knime.types.RDKitMolCellFactory

  • public final class RDKitMolCellFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    Factory creating RDKitMolValue compatible DataCell objects. It's currently using RDKitMolCell2; future versions may return different implementations (e.g. blobs).
    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland, Manuel Schwarze, NIBR

    • Method Detail

      • createRDKitMolCell

        public static DataCell createRDKitMolCell(ROMol mol)
        Creates a new RDKit Cell based on the given molecule. The argument can (and should) be deleted after this method returns.
        Parameters:
        mol - the ROMol value to store
        Returns:
        A data cell implementing RDKitMolValue interface. Currently this is a RDKitMolCell2 but this may change in future versions.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if argument is null

      • createRDKitMolCell

        public static DataCell createRDKitMolCell(ROMol mol,
                                          java.lang.String smiles)
        Creates a new RDKit Cell based on the given molecule and SMILES. The argument can (and should) be deleted after this method returns.
        Parameters:
        mol - the ROMol value to store
        smiles - canonical SMILES for the molecule
        Returns:
        A data cell implementing RDKitMolValue interface. Currently this is a RDKitMolCell2 but this may change in future versions.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if argument is null

      • createRDKitAdapterCell

        public static DataCell createRDKitAdapterCell(ROMol mol)
        Creates a new RDKit Adapter Cell with an RDKit Mol Cell based on the given molecule. A canonicalized SMILES will be created as part of the inner RDKit Cell. The argument can (and should) be deleted after this method returns.
        Parameters:
        mol - the ROMol value to store
        Returns:
        A data cell implementing RDKitMolValue interface. Currently this is a RDKitAdapterCell but this may change in future versions.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if argument is null

      • createRDKitAdapterCell

        public static DataCell createRDKitAdapterCell(ROMol mol,
                                              java.lang.String smiles)
        Creates a new RDKit Adapter Cell with an RDKit Mol Cell based on the given molecule and SMILES. The argument can (and should) be deleted after this method returns.
        Parameters:
        mol - the ROMol value to store
        smiles - SMILES for the molecule. This SMILES will be taken as is and flagged as non-canonical in the inner RDKit Cell.
        Returns:
        A data cell implementing RDKitMolValue interface. Currently this is a RDKitAdapterCell but this may change in future versions.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if argument is null

      • createRDKitAdapterCellAndDelete

        public static DataCell createRDKitAdapterCellAndDelete(ROMol mol)
        Creates a new RDKit Adapter Cell based on the given molecule and discards the argument using the ROMol#delete() method. A canonicalized SMILES will be created as part of the inner RDKit Cell.
        Parameters:
        mol - the ROMol value to store
        Returns:
        A data cell implementing RDKitMolValue interface. Currently this is a RDKitAdapterCell but this may change in future versions.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if argument is null
